        <p class="bk-notes en">The words of "Dangnian Mingyue" have, to some extent, influenced my writing style. As a result, in my current writings, serious narratives often have to be interspersed with a touch of jest. However, it is precisely under this seemingly relaxed and even slightly casual writing style that I unexpectedly touched upon a long-lost idealistic light. From Wang Yangming's philosophy of the mind and the unity of knowledge and action, to Hai Rui's straightness and integrity, and then to Zhang Juzheng's weighing and reform, countless people have never bowed their heads, each following a different path, trudging alone in the crevices of power, morality and history, yet always holding fast to that beam of ideal light in their hearts.</p>
        <p class="bk-notes zh" style="display:none">当年明月的文字在某种程度上影响了我的文风，以至于我现在的文字里，往往严肃的叙述偏要夹杂几分戏谑。然而正是在这种看似轻松甚至略显随意的笔触之下，我却意外地触碰到一种久违的理想主义光芒，从王阳明的心学与知行合一，到海瑞的刚直与清廉，再到张居正的权衡与改革...无数人未曾低首，各自循着不同的路径，在权力、道德与历史的缝隙之间踽踽而行，却始终紧握心中的那一束理想之光</p>
