    <div class="bk-author zh" style="display:none">纳兰性德，清代</div>

    <div class="bk-rating">★★★★★</div>

    <p class="bk-notes en">
      Nalan Xingde's poems were successively compiled into "Side Hat" and "Drinking Water", and later generations mostly referred to them as Nalan's poems. Looking at Nalan Xingde's poetic style, it is fresh and elegant, with a touch of melancholy and playful beauty, quite similar to that of the last Emperor of the Southern Tang Dynasty. He himself also greatly admired Li Yu. He once said, "Words spoken among flowers are like ancient jade wares, precious but not applicable." The lyrics of the Song Dynasty are practical yet rare and precious, while Li Houzhu combines them and has its own beauty, and is even more steeped in the misty and enigmatic charm.
    </p>

    <p class="bk-notes zh" style="display:none">
      纳兰性德词作先后结集为《侧帽》、《饮水》，后人多称纳兰词。纵观纳兰性德词风，清新隽秀、哀感顽艳，颇近南唐后主。而他本人也十分欣赏李煜，他曾说：花间之词如古玉器，贵重而不适用；宋词适用而少贵重，李后主兼而有其美，更饶烟水迷离之致。
    </p>

