      <div class="bk-rating">★★★★★</div>
  
      <p class="bk-notes en">
        Nietzsche’s words feel less like arguments and more like detonations. “God is dead” is not a celebration, but a diagnosis — and what follows is a silence we are still learning how to endure. In that silence, the question is no longer what is true, but whether we can still create meaning.
      </p>
  
      <p class="bk-notes zh" style="display:none">
        尼采的文字更像是引爆，而不是论证。“上帝已死”并非宣告胜利，而是一种诊断——随之而来的，是人必须独自承受的空白。在这片空白之中，问题不再是“什么是真的”，而是“我们是否还能创造意义”。
      </p>
  
