      <div class="bk-title zh" style="display:none">《查拉图斯特拉如是说》— 尼采</div>
  
      <div class="bk-author en">Friedrich Nietzsche, 1883–1885</div>
      <div class="bk-author zh" style="display:none">尼采，1883–1885</div>
  
      <div class="bk-rating">★★★★★</div>
  
      <p class="bk-notes en">
        After “God is dead,” Nietzsche does not leave us in silence — he demands a response. Zarathustra speaks not to explain the world, but to ask whether we can become something beyond what we are. The question is no longer about truth, but about creation.
      </p>
  
      <p class="bk-notes zh" style="display:none">
        在“上帝已死”之后，尼采并没有让人停留在沉默之中，而是逼迫人作出回应。查拉图斯特拉不是在解释世界，而是在追问：人能否成为超越自身之物？问题不再关乎真理，而关乎创造。
      </p>
  
